annotation.TEXT: And just like that, blue wins, without red even getting one hit! I think I'm going to let this keep going until red gets at least one hit, though.
Yeah, I was just confirming that cape spins don't work on them.
Oops, I should've taken the upper route this time for the Yoshi coin. I'd better go back around for it.
Well, I didn't get hit there, but... I'll still have to make the return trip.
And this is just a dead-end with eight more coins, but at least they're not unreasonable to reach.
Cool. I killed something below the screen with that shot.
Bah! I knew I was going to get hit there somehow! I really hate these spike balls...
Well, that was underwhelming.
Hey, it's a P-switch. Yep, where there's puzzles, there's usually P-switches. Can I reach this one from here?
Not by bouncing off of Blargg (which was a little risky). I'll probably need to find a springboard somewhere.
Okay, at least I get a replacement cape here. (Of course, if that dumb hit hadn't happened, I'd have two capes now.)
Hey there everyone, and welcome back to Bowser Rampages Again!

To answer that question up there, it depends. If it starts off as a non-green baby Yoshi or comes from a block, then the egg came first. For a green baby Yoshi or a Yoshi that doesn't come from a block, then the Yoshi comes first. (I think. Correct me if I'm wrong.)
Yay, happy music!
Hmm... Maybe I walled off red a little too well...
Okay, I managed to lose the RVF here. Good thing it's not so unreasonable for a small plumber to get through these spike ball passages, but good luck if you're big.
I'll save this yellow ! block just in case I take a dumb hit in the near future.
Whoa! That RVF almost took me by surprise!
I just gotta make sure no Buzzies get in my way...
And now for Deep Caverns 2, since it's currently the only new place I can go to.
That was way too close. Those six coins were not worth it.
That was almost dangerous up there...
Whoa, good thing I had the cape to help me get that last Yoshi coin! That would've sucked so much if I had missed it! (And yes, I would've replayed the entire level for it.)
I think I'll go to ludicrous speed for a second for this bonus game...

Oh, I guess this is where you'd use the P-switch, and if I had to guess, judging by what's ahead, I'd say that that ? block has a star. Of course, I don't have to guess, since I already know it holds a star!
I think I'll be more patient here while watching the walls try to crush a Buzzy.
Uh, oh. More layer 2 shenanigans, this time involving rising and falling lava.
Yep, there's no going back up from here.
Oh, man. A Fire Brother. They can be tricky...
Blue Switch Palace
Okay, I just proved that blue ! blocks don't hold any items.
Looks like it's time for layer 2 shenanigans...
Yes, I saw that RVF down there. I will be ready for him.
More undead guys. I'll just avoid the gray ones since I don't have a weapon to kill them with.
Oh, nuts. That's right, this place brings back those awful spike balls from before. This is probably going to be a pain...
What? No "hurry up" sound effect? Is it because of the cape-flight sound effect occurring at that exact time?
Whew! Thankfully, I'm done with this unusually tricky Switch Palace!
Yep, so as expected, the Blue Switch Palace won! (I have no idea what I would've done if red somehow won during that biased tie-breaker...)
Go away, Rip Van Fish!
Okay, I got the P-switch, but I kind of want to hold onto the springboard for some reason. Hmm... Maybe I can stomp the P-switch now and race to the ? block?
Slow-motion shell jump!
Oh, wow. You can kill those gray duders with a shell attack! I guess they're not so immortal...
Jump to about 2:20 in the video if you just want to skip to where I resume playing.
There wasn't very much margin of error there, but I made it.
Well, at least these six coins aren't that unreasonable to collect.
Oh, man. Going for these coins is a bad idea!
BGM: Tetris Attack (SNES) - Bowser's Theme
Oh, I guess flying was unnecessary.
Yoshi coin below. Gotta go back around and get it.
This Yoshi coin would definitely be trickier to reach without a cape.

Well, that stunk, but whatever. I'm at 99 lives anyway. It's interesting how the game only gradually disables your controls at the end of the bonus game. For instance, the down direction becomes disabled immediately upon me touching the last 1-up, but I can still make other movements for a couple seconds.
Yeah, all that's here are eight measly coins. It's totally not worth it. Maybe if there was a power-up, 1-up, or MOON, I'd consider going here more worthwhile...
Hmm... Which way should I go? Uhh... Just pick a direction already!
Ooh, over that way is a 1-up. Okay, I think I'll work my way back over there.
Looks like I've only got one new place to go to right now... The castle! But, that'll have to wait until next time!

Oh, I'm just now noticing that WhiteYoshiEgg symbol etched into the dirt (and looking back, there have been a bunch of those in the cave levels' dirt). So, I'm guessing he must've had a hand in making this hack?
Okay, I've got my springboard, but what's to the right?
Yes! Okay, one cloning is enough for me right now.
And now to wait a few seconds for the wall to move out of the way so I can continue downwards...
May as well collect these six coins since they're simple enough to get.
Surprisingly, this 1-up and these nine coins seemed easier to reach than those eight coins at the start.
Thwack!
Now, this is actually a health risk. A super plumber that duck-jumps onto that highest block and then stands upright will eventually get pulled into the wall on the left and get crushed to death.
To be continued...
Whoops! So much for that shell, but then again, it did serve me quite well, and protected me from a hit there.

So, last time, I was left with a choice between the Blue Switch Palace and Deep Caverns 2, and I had you guys vote to determine which level I'm gonna play next. Now, I wonder which level ended up winning... Let's find out...
If I fail, at least I've got reset doors!
Oh, man. There's coins in that passage on the far right.

I hit the goal low there to make sure that the cape from that springboard I babysat all this way wouldn't get stuck in the ceiling. (Also, I managed to time it so that the numbers lined up for a free life that I don't need. Huzzah!)
Interestingly, Fire Duders are not fireproof. They're totally flammable and inflammable!
Yeah, I had plenty of time. Now, let's grab this star and rampage across these munchers!
Okay, this is probably a power up block, and yes, I'm going to try to clone it.
Ooh, nice. A cape.
Screen transition?
Yep, I got hurt there. You've gotta be almost pixel-perfect to get a super-sized plumber through there unharmed. What do they call that? "Big Mario discrimination"?
Okay, seriously. Look at this very narrow 2-space high passage between the spike balls that I've gotta swim through.
I see a passage I might want to fly up!
There's midpoint. Zwee!
And now, I'm totally defenseless against the sea life here, so all I can do is try to evade everything.
Wah! Who didn't see something like that coming? That totally qualifies as a dumb hit! (I shouldn't have touched that yellow ! block yet.)
And now that I've said that, I'm expecting to take a dumb hit shortly, but we'll see...
That opens up Deep Caverns 3, and yeah, I feel like doing another level right now, so let's do this!
Go my blue blocks, and make everything blue! (Or just fill in specific dotted blocks in certain places throughout the land.)
Uh, oh. Those undead immortal duders are back.
Outta the way, pencils! Ooh, why can't I simply just tear through them while invincible?
Okay, that dead-end was worth 20 coins, but come on, no power up? You know what would've been really awesome in one of these dead-ends? A star!
Looks like I'll be switching power ups as I deem fit here.
BGM: Touhou 11 - Rin's Theme - Corpse Voyage ~ Be of good cheer!
More blue ! blocks...
Okay, it looped, so I'm outta here!
Oh, so there's some puzzle action going on in this cave, eh?
Deep Caverns 2
Hmm... Now there's gonna be some solid land moving along layer 2, eh?
Hmm... I wonder...
Screw it. I'm getting this mushroom now, since I no longer expect to take a dumb hit here. (Did I just jinx myself?)
Oh, but... Look at what I have to squeeze through to get over there! I'm probably going to regret this, but... I'm gonna go for it!
Yay, a blue ! block! It made that pit very slightly easier to jump over!
Woo, I did that kind of dangerously!
ASDFASDFASDF...

And now for several seconds of silence, because the victory music is so short, but I still have to wait the usual amount of time. (Is it possible to decrease the waiting time after hitting a palace switch?)
Ooh, there's a red hit, finally. However, this is good custom music, so I think I'll let this keep going until it loops once. (That should end up being over a minute of good custom music...)
Hi, Chuck! Bye, Chuck!
So, I guess this place will be water-themed...
Yep, I'm going with Zeldara109's tie-breaker room idea here! The left shell will represent the Blue Switch Palace, while the right shell represents Deep Caverns 2. First one to get a 1-up wins!
These nine coins are 50% more worth it, but still not really worth it.
